North doorway 0.94 m in width; depth into Trench 126 = 0.99 m; south doorway (partially excavated) width 0.84 m, depth 0.81 m on the west.
In the partition wall between Trench 127 Chamber 3 and Trench 126.
Phase XII: Use levels, robbing and abandonments continue.

Phase XI: Further collapse post- CE 5th c., possibly the result of the earthquake of CE 512. Major collapses in the Lower Temenos lead to the continued accumulation of fill. At this time the East Colonnade collapses significantly onto a bed of accumulated soil, as does the entablature of the East Exedra.
Locus 19 collapse and debris and the Trench 127 and Trench 126 partition wall.
The collapse debris Locus 19, but earlier.
The Munsell color of this deposit is Brown 7.5YR5/3 and it is a destruction deposit filled with bricks, cement and mortar.
North doorway height: 1.21 m; south doorway height: 1.17 m.
